I found exactly what you need. The type definitions in `@stricli/core@1.2.5` confirm full support for hiding routes/commands from help output. Here is a comprehensive summary of the findings.

---

## Library: @stricli/core (v1.2.5)

### 1. Hiding Routes from Help Output via `hideRoute`

The `RouteMapDocumentation` interface (lines 1394-1407 of the type definitions) includes a `hideRoute` property specifically designed for this purpose.

**Type definition** (from `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/albuquerque/node_modules/.bun/@stricli+core@1.2.5/node_modules/@stricli/core/dist/index.d.ts`, lines 1394-1407):

```typescript
interface RouteMapDocumentation<R extends string> {
    /**
     * In-line documentation for this route map.
     */
    readonly brief: string;
    /**
     * Longer description of this route map's behavior, only printed during `--help`.
     */
    readonly fullDescription?: string;
    /**
     * Each route name with value `true` will be hidden from all documentation.
     */
    readonly hideRoute?: Readonly<Partial<Record<R, boolean>>>;
}
```

**Usage**: In the `docs` property of `buildRouteMap`, set `hideRoute` with route names mapped to `true` to hide them. For example, to hide the `whoami` command from `--help` output in your CLI:

```typescript
const routes = buildRouteMap({
    routes: {
        login: loginCommand,
        logout: logoutCommand,
        whoami: whoamiCommand,
        upload: uploadCommand,
    },
    docs: {
        brief: "CLI tools for managing Claude Code sessions",
        hideRoute: {
            whoami: true,  // This command will not appear in --help output
        },
    },
});
```

The `hideRoute` property is type-safe -- it only accepts keys that are actual route names defined in the `routes` object (the generic `R extends string` is inferred from the routes).

### 2. The `--helpAll` Flag Reveals Hidden Commands

Stricli has a built-in `--helpAll` (or `--help-all` with kebab-case scanning) flag that shows **all** documentation, including hidden commands and flags. This is always available but is itself hidden from normal `--help` output by default.

From the `DocumentationConfiguration` interface (lines 421-461):

```typescript
interface DocumentationConfiguration {
    /**
     * In addition to the `--help` flag, there is a `--helpAll`/`--help-all` flag
     * that shows all documentation including entries for hidden commands/arguments.
     * The `--helpAll` flag cannot be functionally disabled, but it is hidden when
     * listing the built-in flags by default.
     * Setting this option to `true` forces the output to always include this flag
     * in the list of built-in flags.
     *
     * Defaults to `false`.
     */
    readonly alwaysShowHelpAllFlag: boolean;
    // ...
}
```

From the `DocumentationBriefs` interface (lines 145-171):

```typescript
readonly helpAll: string;
// Defaults to: "Print help information (including hidden commands/flags) and exit"
```

This means:
- `--help` will **not** show hidden routes
- `--helpAll` / `--help-all` **will** show hidden routes (and this cannot be disabled)
- If you want `--helpAll` to appear in normal help output, set `alwaysShowHelpAllFlag: true` in the application documentation config

### 3. Hidden Flags (Individual Parameters)

Flags can also be hidden individually by setting `hidden: true` on the flag parameter definition. This is available for:

- **Optional flags**: Any optional flag can set `hidden: true` (lines 620-624)
- **Required flags with defaults**: A required flag can be hidden only if it has a `default` value (lines 600-614)

Example:

```typescript
buildCommand({
    func: myFunc,
    parameters: {
        flags: {
            debug: {
                kind: "boolean",
                brief: "Enable debug mode",
                optional: true,
                hidden: true,  // Won't appear in --help, only in --helpAll
            },
        },
    },
    docs: { brief: "My command" },
});
```

### 4. Hidden Routes in Completion Proposals

The `CompletionConfiguration` interface (lines 465-478) also controls whether hidden routes appear in tab-completion:

```typescript
interface CompletionConfiguration {
    /**
     * This flag controls whether or not to include hidden routes.
     *
     * Defaults to `false`.
     */
    readonly includeHiddenRoutes: boolean;
}
```

By default, hidden routes are excluded from completions as well. You can override this in `buildApplication`:

```typescript
export const app = buildApplication(routes, {
    name: "rudel",
    completion: {
        includeHiddenRoutes: true,  // Include hidden routes in tab-completion
    },
    // ...
});
```

### Summary

| Mechanism | Where | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `docs.hideRoute: { routeName: true }` | `buildRouteMap` | Hides entire route/command from `--help` |
| `hidden: true` on flag parameter | `buildCommand` parameters | Hides individual flag from `--help` |
| `--helpAll` / `--help-all` | Built-in flag (always active) | Reveals all hidden commands and flags |
| `alwaysShowHelpAllFlag: true` | `buildApplication` documentation config | Makes `--helpAll` visible in normal `--help` |
| `includeHiddenRoutes: true` | `buildApplication` completion config | Includes hidden routes in tab-completion |

The key file in your project that would need modification is `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/douala/apps/cli/src/app.ts` -- you would add `hideRoute` to the `docs` object inside `buildRouteMap`.

